HEADWORD: Triquetrous
<hw>Tri*que"trous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>triquetrus</ets>.]</ety> <def>Three sided, the sides being plane or
concave; having three salient angles or edges; trigonal.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

